criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Provision of written informed consent;

          -  Ages 40-60 years old;

          -  Right handed.

          -  If female, not pregnant (as determined by a positive pregnancy test); and agrees to
             use one of the following methods of birth control: abstinence from sexual
             intercourse, barrier (diaphragm or condom), or oral/injectable contraceptive;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Contraindication to an MRI scan (i.e., braces, claustrophobia, pacemaker etc);

          -  A history of a major medical (e.g., diabetes) or neurological illness (e.g.,
             epilepsy);

          -  Body mass index (BMI) â‰¥ 30;

          -  An IQ <75 and >130;

          -  A positive urine drug test (nicotine dependence is permitted);

          -  Personal history of a DSM-5 Axis I psychiatric disorder;

          -  Requiring treatment with a drug which might obscure the action of the study
             treatment.
